Yea, it sure is the shits, Doc. But, I don't see myself pushing anybody away. In fact, I am surprised at how this has taken off, and it frustrates me to no end, because there is so much to deal with and we waste our time on something as insignificant as this, not to mention, cyberspace, of which you and I are NOT paying for. I mean, are we done dealing with racism and the Vietnamese-Americans, attitudes, experiences, etc. I don't believe so, but if I'm out numbered, then, again, let's let this thread die and move on to other issues.<br><br>
I don't think I'm being hostile to anyone. With Chet, I appreciated his concerns, but tried to reassure him that I am OK. I am a little taken aback and disappointed that he thinks I would frag him because he confronted me. With you, Doc, I just accept who you are, and figured I was seeing old habits break hard. What I wrote to Betty was not an attack, but observations only. I still will engage you anytime, whether in agreement, or disagreement. As I told you before, I reserve the right to jump on you ass in any which way I do, but that does not negate our friendship. Not on my end, anyway. At the heigth of my anger towards you, Doc, I never, not once threw you overboard. I would have smashed this computer over your head more than once, but I never abandoned you. I have allowed you folks your say without hostility because I understand where it comes from, but for the last time, it started with your erroneous premise. I have responded to each and everyone of you as appropriately as I can. There were no FUCK YOU'S in any of them, just a plead to let us move on.<br><br>
As far as being touchy, I tried the best I can to deal with what you folks laid out for me in a clear, concise and appropriate manner. How is that being touchy? Touchy is what I threw at you about the Jewish business. Touchy is how I slammed that individual on the &quot;Protestors&quot; thread when he accused us of playing intellectual games. I don't see it here.<br><br>
I will allow that I may have just a microscopic smiggen of a problem with what you speak, the closeness issue, and with compliments, but I don't see this place as a place for compliments whether on my writings or on people's personal web sites, or what I am wearing today. And I agree that that may be a problem of mine that I, alone, own. I feel that that is what e-mail is for. In the last week, I e-mailed Chet and John Ratliff and others and thanked them for their friendship and tried to pay them tribute the best way I could. The tribute I pay you is still being your friend. (that is a Joke!)Same-same with humor. But, again, for the life of me, I see no humor in what we discuss. Again, probably something that I alone, own. I accept this.<br><br>
I have re-read my posts to Chet and to Betty and I don't see where I could have hurt them, however, it is my hope that they do not read anything vicious or any personal attacks because it is not in there! I have given Chet the one most important thing in my life, and the highest compliment that I could have. I have done this with Betty, also.<br><br>
And finally, to finish(god, I hope so), I agree that I am as fucked up, or more to be exact, more fucked up than all of you combined. With this, and all the other concessions that I had made above, can we, PLEASE, move on?<br><br>
Are you finished with the issue with your trip to Little Saigon and the Wall? I had read that you left room to come back with more on this subject. And, no, I am not trying to change the subject, just trying, in my own feeble way, of getting us back on track.
